### Deploy Hook Parameter

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/deploy-button/callback

The Deploy Hook parameter enables automatic redeployment of user projects by creating a Deploy Hook during project creation. When combined with a Redirect URL, you receive the deploy hook URL as a callback parameter upon successful deployment.

```APIDOC
## Deploy Hook Parameter

### Description
Configure a Deploy Hook during project creation to receive a URL for redeploying user projects. Useful for applications like headless CMS systems that need to trigger rebuilds when content changes.

### Query Parameter
- **production-deploy-hook** (string) - Optional - The name of the Deploy Hook to create

### Requirements
- The `redirect-url` parameter must also be set
- Deploy Hook will be created automatically during project setup

### Usage Example
```
https://vercel.com/new/clone?repository-url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fvercel%2Fnext.js%2Ftree%2Fcanary%2Fexamples%2Fhello-world&redirect-url=https%3A%2F%2Fmy-headless-application.com&production-deploy-hook=MyHeadlessProject
```

### Parameters
- **repository-url** (string) - Required - The GitHub repository URL to clone
- **redirect-url** (string) - Required - Your application URL to redirect to after deployment
- **production-deploy-hook** (string) - Optional - The name of the Deploy Hook to create

### Callback Response
Upon successful deployment, you will receive the following callback parameter:
- **production-deploy-hook-url** (string) - The URL to trigger redeployment of the project

Plus all default callback parameters from the project creation flow.
```

