### Adding script using DOM API in Next.js (Caught by rule)

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/conformance/rules/NEXTJS_USE_NEXT_SCRIPT

This example shows a script being dynamically inserted into the DOM using `document.createElement('script')` and `appendChild()`. The `NEXTJS_USE_NEXT_SCRIPT` rule flags this pattern because it bypasses Next.js's optimized script loading mechanisms provided by `next/script`.

```tsx
function insertScript() {
  const script = document.createElement('script');
  script.src = process.env.SCRIPT_PATH;
  document.body.appendChild(script);
}
```

