### Deploy Hook Parameter Configuration

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/llms-full

Configure a Deploy Hook parameter to receive a URL for redeploying user projects. This is useful for headless CMS integrations or applications that need to trigger project rebuilds when content changes. Requires the Redirect URL parameter to be set.

```APIDOC
## Deploy Hook Parameter

### Description
Sets up a Deploy Hook that receives a URL for redeploying user projects upon successful deployment. Commonly used with headless CMS applications to automatically rebuild projects on content changes.

### Parameters

#### Query Parameters
- **production-deploy-hook** (string) - Required - The name of the Deploy Hook to set up for the user
- **redirect-url** (string) - Required - The redirect URL to return to after deployment, paired with this parameter

#### Callback Parameters
- **production-deploy-hook-url** (string) - Provided in callback upon successful deployment alongside default callback parameters

### Request Example
```
https://vercel.com/new/clone?repository-url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fvercel%2Fnext.js%2Ftree%2Fcanary%2Fexamples%2Fhello-world&redirect-url=https%3A%2F%2Fmy-headless-application.com&production-deploy-hook=MyHeadlessProject
```

### Response
- **production-deploy-hook-url** (string) - The Deploy Hook URL returned upon successful deployment
- Additional default callback parameters included in redirect response

### Notes
- This parameter requires the Redirect URL parameter to be set
- Useful for CMS integrations and applications requiring project redeployment
```
